main event: Sighting of thirteen unidentified aerial objects over Miami, Florida on May 19, 1955.
interesting points: The main object had a dome and remained motionless for 13 minutes., Twelve of the objects moved too fast for detail., The total sighting duration was about 15 minutes., The witness reported that the object disappeared and reappeared at times., The witness had previously seen similar objects several times in the past two years.
witness description: Male, 26 years old, with a history of interest in unidentified objects.
